main event: A civilian observed a round object pass overhead at Yorktown, Virginia in 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as being larger than a conventional aircraft and emitting no sound.
It passed from horizon to horizon in 1-3 seconds and left no apparent trail.
The description is consistent with that of a meteor observation.
Another witness observed two oval-shaped objects that were extremely bright, circulating, and had an intense light trailing after them.
The witness sketched the objects and asked if there was a natural explanation for the observation, stating they had not reported it to any newspaper and would prefer to have their name unpublicized.
